The Core Principles
âš™ï¸ 1. Prediction Minimizes Surprise
The brain is a Bayesian inference engine, not a passive receiver.
2. Conscious Access Requires Ignition
Most processing is unconscious; consciousness is selective
broadcasting.
3. Habits Form Through Spiral Architecture
Limbic (value) â†’ Associative (goal) â†’ Sensorimotor (habit).
4. Dopamine Teaches, Not Rewards
Prediction error drives learning; habituation kills motivation.
5. Memory is Reconstructive and Updatable
Retrieval + mismatch = opportunity for change.
6. Emotion is Constructed, Not Triggered
Body state + context + concept = subjective feeling.
7. Plasticity is Expensive
The brain resists change unless surprise justifies cost.
8. Fatigue is Neurochemical Status
Glutamate accumulation, NE depletion, cytokine signaling.
